Sentencas: In this study, porous Cu-YSZ cermets with various Cu contents are fabricated and their crystal structure and morphological features are investigated by X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural properties of porous Cu-YSZ cermets for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Carbon black-containing CuO/Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) composites exhibit a highly porous structure due to the evolution of CO and CO2 gasses during sintering.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural properties of porous Cu-YSZ cermets for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The porosity of the CuO/YSZ composites decreases with increases of the sintering temperature and CuO content.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural properties of porous Cu-YSZ cermets for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Highly porous Cu/YSZ cermets are fabricated by reducing the porous CuO/YSZ composites in (Ar + 6% H-2) atmosphere.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural properties of porous Cu-YSZ cermets for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Higher CuO content and higher sintering temperature reduce the porosity of Cu/YSZ cermets after reduction treatment.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural properties of porous Cu-YSZ cermets for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microstructure and porosity of Cu/YSZ cermets as an anode material are remarkably affected by the CuO content, sintering temperature, and carbon black content.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural properties of porous Cu-YSZ cermets for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: We believe that the porous Cu/YSZ cermets are a promising anode material for high performance of SOFC.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural properties of porous Cu-YSZ cermets for solid oxide fuel cells
